```java
boolean isAssignedOnceInLifetime() {
  Reference ref = getOneAndOnlyAssignment();
  if (ref == null) {
    return false;
  }

  // Make sure this assignment is not in a loop.
  for (BasicBlock block = ref.getBasicBlock();
       block != null; block = block.getParent()) {
    if (block.isFunction) {
      // If the variable is defined in this function, its lifetime
      // is limited to this function call, so we can stop.
      // Otherwise, we need to continue because the variable might be
      // assigned multiple times if the function is called from a loop.
      if (block.getFunction() == this.getScope().getRootNode()) {
        break;
      }
    } else if (block.isLoop) {
      return false;
    }
  }

  return true;
}
```

